# Matriarch Library Rules

## Stack
- Java 21, Maven, JUnit 5
- No Lombok — this is a published library with no external annotation processors
- Dependencies: Jackson, SnakeYAML, Reflections

## Architecture
- Entry point: Mother.forClass(T.class) → fluent builder → .build()
- Core generation in domain/core/
- Domain model in domain/model/ (Overrider, Definition, Coordinate, Pattern)
- Suppliers in suppliers/ organized by category (address, company, datetime, etc.)
- JUnit 5 integration in junit/annotations/

## Conventions
- forField() is the preferred API; override() is a legacy alias for backward compatibility
- Suppliers are organized by domain category, each with a single responsibility
- Override precedence: forField value > forField supplier > forType supplier > pattern matching > random
- Known patterns: System Properties > YAML config > built-in defaults
- Maintain backward compatibility for all public API changes
- Keep dependency footprint minimal
- Use Java records in tests but support generating any POJO type

## Build
- ./mvnw clean install (build + test)
- ./mvnw test (tests only)
- Published to Maven Central via Sonatype with GPG signing
